always would say,

03:44.224 --> 03:46.617
"Don't you ever let
a man disrespect you."

03:49.794 --> 03:51.579
I figured that's probably
why she left you.

03:52.319 --> 03:54.234
Talk about disrespect.

03:54.408 --> 03:56.148
You made a fool
of her.

03:57.585 --> 04:01.197
And then what?
We left and then you just

04:01.371 --> 04:04.200
slid over
to your new family?
Is...

04:05.070 --> 04:06.594
I mean, how long were me
and Marcus gone

04:06.768 --> 04:08.248
before you shacked up
with that girl and her mother?

04:08.422 --> 04:09.858
It wasn't like that.

04:10.032 --> 04:13.253
Really? 'Cause... How was it?
Ple... Please tell me.

04:16.604 --> 04:19.084
I remember everything
that you said.

04:19.259 --> 04:21.783
"I'll come see you,
baby girl.

04:21.957 --> 04:24.002
"I'ma come visit you
real soon."

04:28.398 --> 04:30.139
I remember it
because I...

04:32.881 --> 04:37.320
I went over it
over and over

04:37.494 --> 04:40.497
and over again
in my head

04:40.671 --> 04:44.371
trying to figure out
"What did I do wrong?

04:44.545 --> 04:46.329
"What did I do wrong?
What did you..."

04:49.245 --> 04:50.681
"Why doesn't he want
to come visit?"

04:52.422 --> 04:53.467
Syd...

04:54.642 --> 04:56.078
I tried.

04:56.252 --> 04:58.646
♪♪♪♪

05:03.215 --> 05:05.043
When your mother
took you kids to Miami,

05:05.217 --> 05:07.132
I became the bad guy.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.439
Everything was my fault.

05:09.613 --> 05:11.833
I've been looking
for ways to tell you.

05:12.007 --> 05:13.791
Whatever we got here,

05:13.965 --> 05:17.229
our quid pro quo
is not exactly
a stable relationship.

05:17.404 --> 05:18.622
I...

05:19.928 --> 05:21.843
Don't put this on me.

05:22.017 --> 05:23.540
I didn't make you
a bad husband,

05:23.714 --> 05:25.847
and I didn't make you
a bad father.

05:26.021 --> 05:28.937
You created a whole
other family.

05:29.111 --> 05:32.201
What was Mom
supposed to do?Fight.

05:33.289 --> 05:35.204
She was supposed
to stay and fight.

05:35.378 --> 05:36.858
With me,
not against me.

05:37.032 --> 05:39.643
No. You were supposed
to stay and fight!

05:39.817 --> 05:40.992
For us.

05:41.776 --> 05:43.168
For your family.

05:43.343 --> 05:45.040
What kind of man are you?

05:45.214 --> 05:47.259
You didn't...
You didn't visit.

05:47.434 --> 05:49.610
You didn't...
You didn't even call.

05:50.828 --> 05:52.917
I had to step up for Kat.

05:54.092 --> 05:55.050
She was
my responsibility.

05:55.442 --> 05:56.747
So was I.

05:58.009 --> 05:59.489
So was I.

06:00.447 --> 06:03.058
♪♪♪♪

06:08.629 --> 06:10.195
Oh, my God.

06:17.333 --> 06:18.508
You didn't want me.

06:19.857 --> 06:22.382
No... No.

06:22.556 --> 06:23.774
You didn't want me.

06:26.734 --> 06:28.518
I was just disposable.

06:31.521 --> 06:32.653
[SIGHS]

06:39.573 --> 06:40.922
Yeah, that's about right.

06:43.707 --> 06:45.405
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:50.801 --> 06:52.150
Where's Zach?In his room.

06:52.324 --> 06:53.413
What the hell is going on?Are you both okay?

06:53.587 --> 06:54.892
Are you okay?No, we're not okay.

06:55.066 --> 06:56.590
Men with guns
were in this house.

06:56.764 --> 06:57.808
What did you do, Dante?I want... I want to see him.

06:57.982 --> 06:59.288
No. No, no. He's asleep.
Stop, stop.

06:59.462 --> 07:00.724
You're supposed to be done
with all of this.

07:00.898 --> 07:02.073
Look, it's not
my fault, okay?

07:02.247 --> 07:03.771
Of course it's your fault!
You and Ray...

07:03.945 --> 07:05.468
Look, what I need you to do
is get your things together.

07:05.642 --> 07:07.035
Oh, I am
way ahead of you.

07:07.209 --> 07:09.124
I... I am taking Zach
to my aunt's in Scottsdale.

07:09.298 --> 07:11.518
He's my son.
You can't just take him
away from me.

07:11.692 --> 07:13.694
Yes, I can.
The judge said I could.

07:13.868 --> 07:15.217
The only reason I stuck
around here was so

07:15.391 --> 07:16.218
that I didn't have
to do this on my own.

07:16.392 --> 07:17.828
Please.I was so stupid.

07:18.002 --> 07:19.569
What is it... What is it
that you want me to do, huh?

07:21.092 --> 07:23.007
What is it that
you want me to do?

07:23.181 --> 07:25.532
You tell me what that is
that you want me to do
and I can do it for you.

07:28.317 --> 07:29.536
You can say goodbye
to your son.

07:30.058 --> 07:31.538
No!

07:31.712 --> 07:33.496
You will not take my son
away from me.

07:33.670 --> 07:35.324
After men with guns
came to my house?

07:37.369 --> 07:38.370
I won't.

07:39.937 --> 07:41.199
Go say goodbye
to your son.

07:42.418 --> 07:43.941
We're leaving.

07:45.987 --> 07:48.337
♪♪♪♪

08:08.923 --> 08:10.228
You want me
to help you with that?

08:10.402 --> 08:12.100
[CHUCKLES]

08:12.622 --> 08:14.145
[DOOR OPENS]

08:16.234 --> 08:17.497
Which one of you
is the lifeguard?

08:22.240 --> 08:24.199
Stop! Wait!
Stop it!

08:24.373 --> 08:26.331
Stop it!

08:26.506 --> 08:27.942
Stop it!
Stop!

08:32.120 --> 08:33.295
Get out of here.

08:34.122 --> 08:35.253
Just go.

08:37.952 --> 08:39.344
Patch me up,
Baywatch.

08:41.129 --> 08:43.087
♪♪♪♪

08:44.915 --> 08:49.616
♪♪ Oh, no, heaven can't save
my soul

08:49.790 --> 08:52.967
♪♪ Heaven can't save my soul

08:53.141 --> 08:57.667
♪♪ No

08:57.841 --> 09:02.193
♪♪ Oh, no,
heaven can't save my soul ♪♪

09:06.763 --> 09:09.244
Hey. Brought you
a change of clothes.

09:22.779 --> 09:24.564
WOMAN: [ON PA]
Oncology to west ward.

09:24.738 --> 09:25.869
Oncology to west.

09:28.480 --> 09:32.267
I know when all of this
is behind us,

09:32.441 --> 09:34.486
we're gonna have
to talk about the...

09:34.661 --> 09:36.793
Vibrator
I saw in your locker.

09:37.577 --> 09:38.882
I'm a self-soother.

09:43.539 --> 09:44.845
Want to talk about it?

09:45.019 --> 09:46.368
My vibrator?

09:46.542 --> 09:48.239
[CHUCKLES] No.

09:48.413 --> 09:49.676
Emotions.

09:50.241 --> 09:51.939
Oh. Ugh. Oof.

09:54.550 --> 09:56.030
Joseph had a daughter.

09:56.204 --> 09:58.685
She's my...

09:58.859 --> 10:00.251
Half-sister.

10:02.210 --> 10:05.126
I have a half-sister.

10:05.300 --> 10:06.388
Wow.

10:09.043 --> 10:10.784
This is
so embarrassing.

10:11.611 --> 10:12.786
Sorry.

10:13.569 --> 10:14.962
You know, my...
My mom used to

10:15.136 --> 10:18.008
beat the crap
out of us,

10:18.182 --> 10:19.619
me and my little brother,
Nico.

10:19.793 --> 10:22.665
I could take it, you know?
I was a tough kid, but...

10:24.319 --> 10:28.018
Nico was soft.
I don't know.

10:28.192 --> 10:29.672
I guess, um...

10:31.282 --> 10:33.284
I'm just telling you
that you're not alone.

10:35.112 --> 10:37.332
I mean, you're literally
not alone.

10:37.506 --> 10:39.900
Your sister's like
right down the hall.

10:40.074 --> 10:41.031
Too soon?

10:45.383 --> 10:47.211
Oh, God.

10:47.385 --> 10:48.648
Is she gonna
be okay?

10:49.736 --> 10:50.867
That's what they say.

10:52.434 --> 10:53.740
I'm losing.

10:54.915 --> 10:56.264
No.

10:57.265 --> 10:59.484
Your sister's
still alive.

10:59.659 --> 11:01.661
He did not
take her from you.

11:02.836 --> 11:04.272
He failed.

11:05.099 --> 11:06.448
You don't understand.

11:09.669 --> 11:11.671
It's not what Knox tried
to take from me.

11:12.628 --> 11:13.847
That's not what hurts.

11:14.586 --> 11:16.110
It's what she
took from me.

11:17.677 --> 11:18.808
Joseph stayed here.

11:18.982 --> 11:21.245
She was good enough
to raise.

11:21.419 --> 11:22.594
Not me.

11:23.291 --> 11:25.467
♪♪♪♪

11:28.035 --> 11:29.993
She got the life
I was supposed to live.

11:35.259 --> 11:36.478
She took my dad.

11:47.054 --> 11:48.620
What do you
want me to do?

11:53.103 --> 11:54.278
Find Arlo.

11:56.454 --> 11:57.673
Done.

12:03.287 --> 12:05.420
♪♪♪♪

12:28.008 --> 12:29.183
Aah!

12:30.010 --> 12:31.228
Wow.

12:32.229 --> 12:33.665
What a night.

12:33.840 --> 12:35.058
[PILLS RATTLE]

12:39.541 --> 12:40.803
Time to get moving.

12:44.198 --> 12:45.677
All the gauze.

12:45.852 --> 12:47.767
Anything
with blood on it.

12:47.941 --> 12:49.725
There.
In the trash.

12:54.643 --> 12:55.905
Now dump the vodka on it.

13:02.869 --> 13:04.087
Now,
what do you with you?

13:04.522 --> 13:05.828
Just go.

13:06.002 --> 13:07.221
The bandage will hold
until tonight,

13:07.395 --> 13:08.613
but you should get
to a hospital.

13:08.788 --> 13:10.180
Aw, that's no fun.

13:11.225 --> 13:12.792
I know.

13:12.966 --> 13:13.923
Let's play a game.

13:15.577 --> 13:16.796
Just let us go.
Please.

13:16.970 --> 13:18.362
Let you go?

13:19.102 --> 13:20.364
Hmm, nah.

13:20.538 --> 13:21.801
But...

13:22.671 --> 13:24.673
You win this game...

13:24.847 --> 13:26.718
No! Please!...and your boyfriend
lives.

13:26.893 --> 13:27.981
No, no.
Please don't.

13:28.155 --> 13:29.504
How about...

13:31.767 --> 13:33.421
Rock, Paper, Scissors?

13:33.595 --> 13:34.509
What?

13:34.683 --> 13:36.728
Let's go.
Hands up.

13:36.903 --> 13:39.601
Please...Play or he dies!

13:44.345 --> 13:45.607
I'm cool either way.

13:48.088 --> 13:50.481
♪♪♪♪

13:54.964 --> 13:57.314
Rock, paper, scissors,
shoot.

14:00.622 --> 14:02.145
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

14:03.277 --> 14:04.626
You're lucky.

14:05.540 --> 14:07.759
Grab your keys.
Let's go.

14:07.934 --> 14:09.370
Just take it.

14:09.544 --> 14:10.762
I can't drive.

14:12.068 --> 14:14.505
What?
A lot of people don't.

14:14.679 --> 14:16.072
Whatever!
Let's go!

14:22.209 --> 14:24.211
♪♪♪♪

14:27.301 --> 14:31.261
Mr. Duvall,
you never struck me
as a patron of the arts.

14:31.435 --> 14:33.698
This place
is fantastic.

14:34.569 --> 14:36.353
If these walls
could talk.

14:36.527 --> 14:38.399
Imagine
what they've seen.

14:38.573 --> 14:41.445
History is
our greatest teacher.

14:41.619 --> 14:44.884
I can make some calls about
achieving landmark status
with the city, if you...

14:45.058 --> 14:47.234
You know,
my great-grandfather

14:47.408 --> 14:50.628
made his nut
in burlesque shows.

14:50.802 --> 14:54.415
I'm thinking about reviving
the family business.

14:54.589 --> 14:57.679
Live sex shows
on the stage,

14:57.853 --> 15:00.029
chicks in cages
up the wings.

15:00.203 --> 15:03.772
Maybe even something
with animals in the back.

15:03.946 --> 15:05.905
[CHUCKLES]

15:12.128 --> 15:17.046
But you didn't come here
to discuss that
revenue stream, did you?

15:17.220 --> 15:22.399
I came here to discuss
you getting cold feet
about being our supplier.

15:22.573 --> 15:25.272
I've got to be honest,
your lack of faith
is incredibly disheartening.

15:25.446 --> 15:27.622
Mr. Knox will be
disappointed, too.

15:27.796 --> 15:29.929
He lost the stash house.

15:30.103 --> 15:35.586
The police confiscated
$20 million in product.

15:35.760 --> 15:40.896
And your associate, Kobi,
was killed in a DEA raid.

15:41.070 --> 15:44.291
Gabriel Knox's ambitions
were perhaps a...

15:44.465 --> 15:48.208
A tad larger
than his abilities.

15:48.382 --> 15:50.732
His West Coast expansion
has been, uh...

15:51.385 --> 15:53.865
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

15:54.040 --> 15:55.215
Rocky.

15:57.304 --> 16:00.220
I know how it looks,
but you have to understand...

16:00.394 --> 16:02.439
It looks like my product

16:02.613 --> 16:06.313
might be better served
with a different distributor.

16:06.487 --> 16:08.010
These are
minor setbacks.

16:08.184 --> 16:10.273
Any more minor setbacks,

16:10.447 --> 16:14.364
and we'll be happy
to take our business
elsewhere.

16:14.538 --> 16:15.931
Mr. Duvall,

16:16.105 --> 16:18.716
you must understand...Please.

16:18.890 --> 16:21.023
Call me Bishop.[CELL PHONE RINGS]

16:21.197 --> 16:22.416
Bishop.

16:22.590 --> 16:23.678
In times like these,
you have to...

16:23.852 --> 16:25.245
I need to take this.

16:27.812 --> 16:29.727
You look upset.

16:29.901 --> 16:32.165
Perhaps Mr. Knox
should have chosen
someone a little less

16:32.339 --> 16:34.384
emotional for this job.

16:37.300 --> 16:40.782
We will earn
your trust back
in short order.

16:40.956 --> 16:42.044
I guarantee it.

16:42.436 --> 16:43.741
I hope so.

16:43.915 --> 16:45.874
It takes balls
to do this job.

16:47.528 --> 16:49.878
[SPEAKING CHINESE]

16:52.141 --> 16:53.403
PATRICK: ...all the
exculpatory evidence.

16:53.577 --> 16:54.796
Don't wait till
"ready for trial."

16:54.970 --> 16:56.928
I want this conviction
straight up.

16:57.103 --> 16:58.582
Here's the Santa Monica
update you asked for.

16:58.756 --> 17:00.106
Any leads?

17:00.280 --> 17:01.933
Yeah, CCTV of a man
feeling the scene.

17:03.935 --> 17:05.502
Son of a bitch.

17:05.676 --> 17:07.461
You know him?

17:07.635 --> 17:08.853
Thanks for this,
Malcolm.

17:09.028 --> 17:10.594
That'll be all.

17:10.768 --> 17:13.075
♪♪♪♪

17:18.254 --> 17:20.474
WALKER: Yo. McKenna.

17:20.648 --> 17:22.519
We just got an assault/robbery
at a lifeguard tower.
Possible kidnapping.

17:22.693 --> 17:25.479
Santa Monica PD
is kicking at us
because you're BOLO.

17:25.653 --> 17:26.958
Might be your shooter.

17:27.133 --> 17:28.525
Let's roll.

