All right.
Anything you want to tell us

17:32.138 --> 17:34.096
about this Santa Monica thing
before we get there?

17:34.270 --> 17:35.663
No.
Let's just get this guy.

17:35.837 --> 17:37.143
Hey, I don't know what y'all
got into out there,

17:37.317 --> 17:38.622
and I don't know
what's going on with Syd,

17:38.796 --> 17:40.146
but it feels like
we're walking into something.

17:40.320 --> 17:42.887
Look, we didn't exactly
follow protocol,

17:43.062 --> 17:44.889
and now that guy
is out there.

17:45.064 --> 17:46.456
People are in danger.

17:49.198 --> 17:50.721
I want to make it right.

17:50.895 --> 17:52.984
All right, look.
We got your back.

17:53.159 --> 17:55.291
But we need to hear
the whole story
when this case is over.

17:55.465 --> 17:56.901
Okay.

17:59.121 --> 18:00.166
Hey.

18:00.340 --> 18:01.428
We need to talk.

18:05.997 --> 18:07.564
Why didn't you tell me
that Steven Hines was

18:07.738 --> 18:09.523
at the Santa Monica
shooting?

18:09.697 --> 18:11.525
What are you talking about?You know
what I'm talking about.

18:11.699 --> 18:13.135
He's a suspect
in the shooting.

18:13.309 --> 18:15.485
He wasn't the shooter.How do you know that?

18:15.659 --> 18:17.879
Because I do.

18:18.053 --> 18:19.576
Then I assume you also know
that "Steven Hines"
doesn't actually exist.

18:22.013 --> 18:23.232
What's his real name?

18:27.018 --> 18:28.629
Dante Sherman.

18:30.761 --> 18:33.416
He's a...
C.I. of mine.

18:34.548 --> 18:36.202
Your C.I.?
Jesus, Nancy.

18:36.376 --> 18:38.160
He was in our house.

18:38.334 --> 18:41.076
I was gonna tell you when
he crashed your press event.

18:41.250 --> 18:42.904
He was pissed because
some information

18:43.078 --> 18:44.906
he told me
got someone hurt.

18:46.299 --> 18:47.300
I just didn't know
how to say it.

18:48.127 --> 18:50.129
I don't know.
I don't know.

18:50.303 --> 18:52.348
Try... Try that
"A dangerous criminal
is crashing into our lives

18:52.522 --> 18:53.784
"because he's pissed
about something."

18:53.958 --> 18:55.134
Maybe that.

18:55.308 --> 18:56.526
He's a confidential
informant.

18:56.700 --> 18:58.224
I'm not supposed to
talk about them.

18:58.398 --> 18:59.921
I have every right to know
about confidential informants!

19:00.095 --> 19:01.705
I am the god damn
district attorney!

19:01.879 --> 19:03.838
Sorry.

19:04.012 --> 19:05.274
What else
do I need to know?

19:05.883 --> 19:06.971
Nothing.

19:09.409 --> 19:10.758
Nancy,
tell me the truth.

19:11.672 --> 19:13.152
It's just a case.

19:13.761 --> 19:16.067
♪♪♪♪

19:19.070 --> 19:20.768
[MONITORS BEEPING]

19:32.127 --> 19:33.694
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

19:41.571 --> 19:44.226
MAN: [ON PA]
Attending nurse, Room 14.

19:44.400 --> 19:46.097
Attending nurse, Room 14.

19:49.579 --> 19:50.928
Been looking for you.

19:53.017 --> 19:54.541
What did your mother
do for a living?

19:54.715 --> 19:56.804
Excuse me?She was a preschool teacher.

19:56.978 --> 19:59.546
Do you know what a preschool
teacher makes a year?

19:59.720 --> 20:00.938
What are you
talking about?

20:01.112 --> 20:02.723
You remember your house
in Miami?

20:02.897 --> 20:05.291
Do you have any idea
what the mortgage
on that house was?

20:06.161 --> 20:08.511
Do you remember
wanting anything?

20:08.685 --> 20:09.860
A bike?
Dance classes?

20:10.034 --> 20:11.297
Summer camp?

20:11.471 --> 20:12.863
Did your mother
ever tell you no?

20:13.037 --> 20:14.561
Where do you think
that money came from, Syd?

20:14.735 --> 20:17.172
Money isn't a father.

20:17.346 --> 20:18.782
Do you think about
the life you had?

20:18.956 --> 20:22.177
Your mother did not provide
that alone, okay?

20:22.351 --> 20:24.092
And don't you tell me
that I didn't want you.

20:24.266 --> 20:26.486
You were a child living
in your mother's house.

20:26.660 --> 20:28.052
You saw things one way.

20:28.227 --> 20:30.141
Now you're an adult.

20:30.316 --> 20:31.752
So, grow up.

20:32.840 --> 20:35.625
Grow up? I did.

20:35.799 --> 20:37.845
And I was wondering
where the hell you went.

20:38.019 --> 20:40.282
It's not that simple, Sydney.
That's what I'm trying
to show you.

20:40.456 --> 20:42.545
It actually is
that simple.

20:42.719 --> 20:45.592
Either you have a dad
or you don't.

20:46.984 --> 20:48.464
Don't act like you
didn't have a choice.

20:48.638 --> 20:50.118
You could've...
You should have been there.

20:50.292 --> 20:52.207
Well, don't you think
I know that?

20:52.381 --> 20:56.167
Baby, can you just stop
hating me for one minute

20:56.342 --> 20:57.995
and listen to what
I'm trying to tell you?

20:58.169 --> 20:59.475
I wanted
to be there for you.

20:59.649 --> 21:00.694
I wanted to.

21:00.868 --> 21:02.130
But I couldn't.

21:02.304 --> 21:03.610
DOCTOR: Mr. Vaughn.

21:03.784 --> 21:05.046
She's awake.

21:05.873 --> 21:07.657
I... I got to go.

21:07.831 --> 21:09.703
Yeah. Go.

21:13.141 --> 21:16.840
BAINES: So, what time
did you and... Um...I want to say Becky.

21:17.014 --> 21:19.190
No. Betsey?

21:19.365 --> 21:20.583
Wait, you don't...
You don't know her name?

21:20.757 --> 21:22.063
We were just hooking up.

21:22.933 --> 21:24.500
I met her at a bar
up the beach.

21:24.674 --> 21:27.286
She said she knew
of a quiet place.

21:27.460 --> 21:30.114
Next thing I knew,
I was getting
my face smashed in

21:30.289 --> 21:31.551
by some guy with a gun.

21:31.725 --> 21:34.597
I woke up
and he was still there.

21:34.771 --> 21:36.643
He made her get her keys
and they left.

21:37.470 --> 21:39.210
I called 911.

21:39.385 --> 21:42.997
Yo. Lifeguard office says that
our girl is Rebecca Arnold.

21:43.476 --> 21:44.999
Becky.

21:45.173 --> 21:46.348
I knew it was Becky.

21:47.610 --> 21:49.046
What a dick.

21:52.311 --> 21:54.878
♪♪♪♪

21:55.052 --> 21:56.315
ARLO: I need an extraction.

21:57.751 --> 21:59.013
No kidding, Arlo.

21:59.187 --> 22:01.494
I heard all about your mess,

22:01.668 --> 22:05.672
and you literally couldn't
have picked a worse day
to keep [SIGHS] being you.

22:05.846 --> 22:07.761
Were my instructions
not clear before?

22:07.935 --> 22:09.284
I did what you said!

22:09.458 --> 22:10.938
I-I made the offer!

22:11.112 --> 22:13.810
I did not tell you to play
mind games with her.

22:13.984 --> 22:16.422
Or give you intel
on her sister so you could
put a bullet in her

22:16.596 --> 22:18.772
in full view
of two dozen witnesses.

22:18.946 --> 22:20.513
She was supposed to
be leverage.

22:20.687 --> 22:22.732
You don't kill leverage,
Arlo.

22:22.906 --> 22:24.081
Burnett started
all of this.

22:24.255 --> 22:25.735
And I'm finishing it.

22:25.909 --> 22:28.782
Please. M... Ms. Hart.
Y-You're overreacting.

22:28.956 --> 22:31.480
Watch it, Arlo, or you'll be
the second man today

22:31.654 --> 22:33.134
who has told me
how I'm feeling.

22:33.308 --> 22:34.962
Look, I-I didn't... I didn't mean to...

22:35.136 --> 22:37.225
Mr. Knox is done with you.

22:37.399 --> 22:38.835
Done? Wait.
N-n-no.

22:39.009 --> 22:41.360
Ms... Ms. Hart, you...
You got to talk to him.

22:41.534 --> 22:43.187
I can make this right.

22:43.362 --> 22:44.406
You've said that
before.

22:44.580 --> 22:46.321
He'll... He'll go after my parents.

22:46.495 --> 22:49.063
He'll kill everybody I know
just to make sure the next guy

22:49.237 --> 22:51.979
knows exactly what'll happen
if he messes up.

22:52.153 --> 22:55.112
Please.
I-I can fix this.
I-I'm begging you.

22:58.638 --> 23:00.770
I'll talk to Mr. Knox.

23:00.944 --> 23:04.992
But in the meantime,
for the love of God, lay low.

23:05.166 --> 23:06.472
No more dead bodies.

23:06.646 --> 23:07.821
I promise.

23:07.995 --> 23:09.736
Thank you.

23:09.910 --> 23:11.868
♪♪♪♪

23:20.094 --> 23:22.662
Aw, balls.

23:25.099 --> 23:28.842
[DEWOLFE'S GOING MY WAY
PLAYING]

23:29.016 --> 23:31.975
♪♪ I'm on top
of the world today

23:32.149 --> 23:33.150
♪♪ Hip, hip, hooray

23:33.324 --> 23:35.109
♪♪ The sun is out

23:35.283 --> 23:36.589
♪♪ The sky's all blue ♪♪

23:36.763 --> 23:38.547
Hey!

23:39.940 --> 23:41.463
Hi!

23:42.682 --> 23:44.248
Hi, sweetie.

23:45.293 --> 23:46.599
It's for you, Mommy.

23:47.861 --> 23:49.515
Katelyn, did you draw that
by yourself?

23:49.689 --> 23:51.168
Yeah.

23:52.256 --> 23:53.867
Honey, it's beautiful.

23:56.217 --> 23:58.262
JOSEPH: Hey.
I'm here.

23:58.654 --> 24:00.047
Hi, Daddy.

24:00.221 --> 24:01.657
I brought you
some things.

24:01.831 --> 24:03.050
Thank you.

24:07.097 --> 24:08.272
Hi.

24:09.578 --> 24:11.537
Hi, Katherine.
Are you up to talking?

24:11.711 --> 24:13.016
I need to ask
a few questions.

24:13.190 --> 24:15.105
[MONITORS BEEPING]

24:23.331 --> 24:24.463
How do you know Arlo?

24:24.985 --> 24:26.377
I don't.

24:26.552 --> 24:29.076
He called you by name
and you came over.

24:29.250 --> 24:32.122
He spent the day buying
a bracelet at my jewelry shop.

24:32.688 --> 24:34.124
How do you know him?

24:35.474 --> 24:37.301
He said he was
going to hurt
someone close to me.

24:39.390 --> 24:41.218
I... I'm sorry.

24:41.392 --> 24:43.090
I didn't...You didn't know.

24:43.264 --> 24:44.308
No.JOSEPH: Syd.

24:44.483 --> 24:45.875
Do we have to
do this now?

24:46.049 --> 24:47.137
Kat needs her rest.

24:47.311 --> 24:49.400
No. We need to talk.

24:49.575 --> 24:50.750
Alone.

24:51.664 --> 24:52.839
Okay.

24:55.015 --> 24:56.277
[SIGHS]

25:03.806 --> 25:06.113
You must be wondering
how I knew who you were.

25:06.374 --> 25:08.332
Yeah.

25:08.507 --> 25:12.772
At first, when I was little,
I didn't know Dad.

25:12.946 --> 25:15.383
I just thought he was
one of my mom's friends.

25:16.297 --> 25:18.865
And then
when my mom died,

25:19.039 --> 25:23.260
I learned that Joe
was actually my father.

25:23.434 --> 25:26.568
But I knew
he had kids.

25:26.742 --> 25:30.093
So, when I got older,
I did a little
social media stalking.

25:31.791 --> 25:32.966
I was curious.

25:33.619 --> 25:35.098
But I never reached out.

25:35.925 --> 25:37.274
He ever talk
about me?

25:38.275 --> 25:39.799
No.

25:39.973 --> 25:42.497
I think it was
too painful for him.

25:43.280 --> 25:45.108
But you do
have his eyes.

25:46.414 --> 25:47.850
My eyes.

25:48.677 --> 25:50.026
Can you see that?

25:51.767 --> 25:53.726
You may think
that you know me

25:53.900 --> 25:56.076
'cause you saw some pictures
of me online.

25:57.947 --> 26:00.254
When I look at you,
I don't feel anything.

26:00.428 --> 26:01.864
You're nothing to me.

26:02.038 --> 26:04.171
My dad screwed your mom.

26:04.345 --> 26:05.781
Doesn't make us family.

26:05.955 --> 26:07.609
♪♪♪♪

26:07.783 --> 26:09.524
[DOOR OPENS]

26:10.830 --> 26:12.309
[DOOR CLOSES]

26:13.397 --> 26:14.964
Whoa! Hey!
What's going on?

26:15.138 --> 26:16.270
Nothing. I got to go.

26:16.444 --> 26:18.315
Please, don't.
Don't. I, uh...

26:18.489 --> 26:19.708
Look, I...

26:21.144 --> 26:22.493
I brought some things
for Kat.

26:22.668 --> 26:25.322
But I also brought
something for you,

26:25.496 --> 26:26.933
something you should...Keep it.

26:27.107 --> 26:29.239
Come on, please,
just look inside.

26:29.413 --> 26:30.763
Please?

26:30.937 --> 26:32.286
Have a seat, come on.

26:42.122 --> 26:43.340
I, uh...

26:44.994 --> 26:46.343
I saved everything.

26:47.562 --> 26:50.652
At first out of anger,
spite,

26:50.826 --> 26:55.657
but then as years
went on I realized
I was saving it for me,

26:55.831 --> 26:57.964
to remind myself
of the kind of man I was

26:58.138 --> 26:59.530
no matter
what your mother said.

27:00.923 --> 27:02.664
LAX to Miami?

27:02.838 --> 27:05.188
I tried to
be there for you, Syd,

27:05.362 --> 27:08.061
but your mother
wouldn't have it.

27:08.235 --> 27:10.324
So, what's this
supposed to prove?

27:10.498 --> 27:11.847
I was there.

27:12.021 --> 27:13.196
Look.

27:15.808 --> 27:17.723
Dance recitals,

27:17.897 --> 27:19.507
basketball games,

27:20.464 --> 27:21.596
graduation.

27:22.989 --> 27:26.645
I showed up,
but your mother
turned me away.

27:27.863 --> 27:29.299
She called the cops on me

27:29.473 --> 27:31.171
a couple of times.

27:31.345 --> 27:33.826
She did not want me
in your lives.

27:36.567 --> 27:38.265
You never seemed to care
what mom wanted before.

27:38.439 --> 27:39.658
Why...

27:42.617 --> 27:44.488
Why would you back down
when it came to your kids?

27:45.446 --> 27:48.841
Our marriage
wasn't perfect,

27:49.015 --> 27:51.234
but we tried.

27:53.236 --> 27:54.673
Then when I slipped,
I...

27:54.847 --> 27:56.544
Is that
what you're calling it?Hey.

27:58.024 --> 28:00.461
When I cheated
on your mother,

28:00.635 --> 28:02.768
the only way she could
make me understand

28:02.942 --> 28:08.251
how bad I hurt her
was to take my world away,

28:08.425 --> 28:09.513
you and your brother.

28:11.298 --> 28:14.736
I broke her heart,

28:14.910 --> 28:16.303
so she took mine.

28:17.913 --> 28:20.916
Eventually I realized
that my showing up

28:21.090 --> 28:24.877
was only hurting her more,
so I stopped.

28:26.008 --> 28:27.357
I just...

28:29.011 --> 28:30.534
Let her
have her revenge.

28:34.147 --> 28:36.584
So if I called Mom
right now

28:36.758 --> 28:38.847
and asked her about
all these trips

28:39.021 --> 28:42.851
and her turning you away,
what would she say?

28:46.072 --> 28:48.901
She'd tell you
she's sorry.

28:50.816 --> 28:52.339
Listen, I...

28:52.513 --> 28:55.211
I didn't tell you this so
you'd be mad with your mother.

28:55.385 --> 28:56.865
I just...

28:59.694 --> 29:01.304
I just want you
to know the truth.

29:04.177 --> 29:05.221
GIRL: Grandpa!

29:05.395 --> 29:06.396
Whoa!

29:06.570 --> 29:08.616
Who let my grandbabies
in here?

29:10.531 --> 29:11.924
Hey, look at you, boy.

29:12.098 --> 29:14.448
You getting so big,
I can barely pick you up.

29:15.579 --> 29:17.059
Hey, son.
How you doing?

29:17.233 --> 29:18.887
♪♪♪♪

29:19.583 --> 29:21.368
You okay? Good.

29:21.542 --> 29:22.586
How you doing, boy?
Look at you!

29:22.761 --> 29:25.546
[CONVERSING INDISTINCTLY]

29:25.720 --> 29:27.722
♪♪♪♪

29:28.941 --> 29:30.203
[SIREN CHIRPS]

29:30.377 --> 29:32.248
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

29:34.381 --> 29:36.165
Yeah, this is it.

29:36.339 --> 29:37.950
It's registered
to Rebecca Arnold.

29:38.124 --> 29:39.125
Yeah, where is she?

29:40.517 --> 29:42.302
There's a lot of blood
up here.

29:42.476 --> 29:43.782
Pop the trunk.

29:50.571 --> 29:53.182
Detectives!
You're gonna
want to hear this.

29:53.356 --> 29:55.663
Looks like
we got something.

29:56.882 --> 29:58.927
I saw it!
He put the gun
right to her head,

29:59.101 --> 30:00.450
and then he shot
that poor girl.

30:00.624 --> 30:02.496
Okay, well, can you describe
the shooter, please?

30:03.410 --> 30:04.411
Short.

30:05.412 --> 30:07.457
Brown, long hair.

30:09.459 --> 30:10.939
Do you know
where he went?

30:11.113 --> 30:13.115
I thought for sure
he was gonna steal the car.

30:13.289 --> 30:15.248
I mean, why else
would he kill that girl?

30:15.422 --> 30:18.338
But he just
put her in the trunk.

30:19.861 --> 30:22.255
He looked around...
He didn't see me,
nobody sees me...

30:22.429 --> 30:24.387
But I watched him.

30:24.561 --> 30:27.477
He just looked at his phone
until a different car
showed up.

30:29.262 --> 30:30.263
That's it?

30:31.394 --> 30:32.874
Yeah, that's it.

30:33.048 --> 30:34.920
He just looked
at his phone?

30:35.094 --> 30:37.400
You said
he's a millennial douchebag.

30:37.574 --> 30:38.837
He took a Phast.Yep.

30:39.011 --> 30:40.708
Let's go. Thank you.Thank you.

30:40.882 --> 30:42.101
I don't care what
the normal lead time is.

30:42.275 --> 30:43.972
I asked for the files
an hour ago.

30:45.452 --> 30:48.324
No, you don't have to ask
your boss,
'cause I'm his boss.

30:48.498 --> 30:49.848
Send them now.

30:53.068 --> 30:54.113
[COMPUTER CHIMES]

30:54.287 --> 30:55.636
Thank you.

31:02.469 --> 31:04.950
♪♪♪♪

31:18.137 --> 31:19.834
I told you,
it's a long shot.

31:20.008 --> 31:21.357
It's the only shot
I got.

31:24.970 --> 31:26.275
Wait.

31:26.449 --> 31:28.408
There,
in the center.

31:28.582 --> 31:31.454
That's it. That's it.
That's the same tattoo
I saw on the sniper's neck.

31:31.628 --> 31:32.629
I knew
I remembered it.

31:32.803 --> 31:34.109
From prison?

31:34.283 --> 31:35.502
Yeah, yeah,
you been inside?

31:35.676 --> 31:37.069
No,
I've not been to prison.

31:37.243 --> 31:38.679
Well, your line of work,
you will.

31:39.854 --> 31:42.552
Now, when you're inside,
you learn things...

31:42.726 --> 31:44.554
Who to sit with,
who to talk to,

31:44.728 --> 31:46.339
and the quickest way
to do that is to clock
the tattoos.

31:46.513 --> 31:49.646
Now, the only gang
that has that tattoo
is from Victorville.

31:49.820 --> 31:51.300
It's the Princes.
So...

31:52.998 --> 31:54.390
Look.

31:54.564 --> 31:57.350
If I do this, you got
to erase my number, okay?

31:57.524 --> 31:59.308
You're in way too deep.

31:59.482 --> 32:00.527
Okay.

32:00.701 --> 32:02.833
♪♪♪♪

32:10.667 --> 32:12.017
There.
That's the one.

32:17.761 --> 32:20.242
♪♪♪♪

32:52.318 --> 32:54.015
I want Arlo.

32:54.189 --> 32:55.930
[STRAINED LAUGH]

32:59.586 --> 33:01.196
[GASPING]

33:05.853 --> 33:07.942
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

33:09.988 --> 33:12.077
♪♪♪♪

34:01.213 --> 34:04.346
♪♪♪♪

34:13.964 --> 34:15.618
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

34:23.452 --> 34:24.714
Dante?

34:24.888 --> 34:26.107
I'm coming for you.

34:28.066 --> 34:30.068
And when I find you,
you're gonna beg
for your life.

34:31.721 --> 34:33.984
And then you're gonna beg me
to let you die.

34:34.159 --> 34:36.248
[LINE CLICKS]

34:46.258 --> 34:47.868
What is going on?

34:48.042 --> 34:49.522
[GROANS]

34:49.696 --> 34:51.654
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]Oh, yeah.

34:57.225 --> 34:59.706
Got him. Tracked him to
his last Phast ride.

34:59.880 --> 35:01.055
He took a Phast ride?

35:01.229 --> 35:02.883
Kids these days.

35:03.057 --> 35:05.015
The kid
is a homicidal maniac.

35:05.190 --> 35:07.061
Yeah, no kidding.
He already killed one girl,

35:07.235 --> 35:08.584
the lifeguard
who patched him up.

35:08.758 --> 35:11.021
We got to get to that driver
before it's too late.

35:11.196 --> 35:12.675
All right,
keep me posted.

35:12.849 --> 35:14.112
How's it going over there?

35:14.286 --> 35:15.200
Bad.

35:15.374 --> 35:17.202
Syd, she died?

35:17.376 --> 35:19.117
No, she didn't.

35:20.205 --> 35:21.728
I guess
it could be worse.

35:23.208 --> 35:24.470
Hey, I got to go.

35:24.644 --> 35:25.906
Uh, let me know
when you find Arlo.

35:26.689 --> 35:27.821
Copy that.

35:30.563 --> 35:31.868
WARREN: Hey.

35:32.042 --> 35:34.001
They told me
I'd find you out here.

35:35.089 --> 35:36.395
You want to talk?No.

35:37.613 --> 35:38.832
Okay.

35:39.833 --> 35:41.226
We'll just stand here,
then...

35:41.400 --> 35:42.401
Silent.

35:46.666 --> 35:48.668
Look, Syd,

35:48.842 --> 35:50.800
I just wanted
to check up on you,
you know?

35:52.889 --> 35:54.674
Make sure you're okay.

35:54.848 --> 35:56.328
Whatever you need,
anything.

35:56.502 --> 35:57.851
Anything
except silence?

35:58.460 --> 35:59.896
Right?Okay.

36:01.246 --> 36:02.508
Why'd you come up here,
Warren?

36:02.682 --> 36:03.900
'Cause
I need the truth.

36:04.074 --> 36:06.294
Why were you
in Santa Monica, Syd?

36:06.468 --> 36:09.297
There was a sniper,
and I know there's more
to the story

36:09.471 --> 36:10.951
than what McKenna fed
the first responders.

36:11.125 --> 36:13.823
I was there
to meet Max's guy,
Arlo.

36:13.997 --> 36:16.435
Okay, but we have
a whole task force now, Syd.

36:16.609 --> 36:17.827
Why go at it alone?

36:18.001 --> 36:20.439
I'm not alone anymore.
I got McKenna.

36:20.613 --> 36:21.962
Yeah...

36:22.136 --> 36:23.485
I saw your pops inside.

36:23.659 --> 36:25.444
I see you got him
in your corner now, too.

36:26.575 --> 36:28.838
I wouldn't exactly
say that.

36:29.012 --> 36:30.971
Look, Syd...

36:32.494 --> 36:35.454
I know
it's none of my business,
but for whatever it's worth,

36:35.628 --> 36:38.370
you should probably cut
your old man some slack.

36:38.544 --> 36:42.765
I mean, last time I saw him,
he was tied up in knots,

36:42.939 --> 36:44.550
the same way he is now,
worried about you.

36:44.724 --> 36:45.812
What are you
talking about?

36:47.640 --> 36:49.555
Okay, so when
the Knox thing
happened,

36:49.729 --> 36:51.992
you were in a coma
for about a week,

36:52.166 --> 36:54.995
and he was right there
sitting at your bedside,

36:55.169 --> 36:56.649
crying his eyes out.

36:56.823 --> 36:58.738
And I was there when Marcus
found your father

36:58.912 --> 37:01.741
sitting right at your bedside,
and he made him go.

37:01.915 --> 37:03.133
It got ugly.

37:03.308 --> 37:05.310
But like I said,
it wasn't my job

37:05.484 --> 37:07.268
to get involved
in family business.

37:07.442 --> 37:11.533
Look, Syd, you got people
that care about you.

37:11.707 --> 37:13.143
Just let them.

37:14.144 --> 37:16.538
♪♪♪♪

37:19.802 --> 37:22.675
[SIREN CHIRPS]

37:29.203 --> 37:31.510
Mr. Kaufman,
Computer Crimes Unit's
pinged your phone.

37:31.684 --> 37:33.425
We need to know
about one of your fares.

37:33.599 --> 37:34.774
You think just 'cause
you're the man

37:34.948 --> 37:35.862
I have to answer
your questions?

37:36.036 --> 37:37.994
Well... Yeah.

37:38.168 --> 37:39.735
Can you step out,
please?

37:41.563 --> 37:43.261
Small guy, long hair.

37:43.435 --> 37:45.741
This is an invasion
of my rights,
invasion of privacy.

37:45.915 --> 37:47.134
I don't consent.

37:47.308 --> 37:49.571
Big Brother can't just
track my movements.

37:49.745 --> 37:52.618
Actually, you did consent
when you signed up to be
a Phast driver, all right?

37:52.792 --> 37:54.402
It's literally
in the contract.

37:55.534 --> 37:57.144
You didn't read me
my rights.

37:57.318 --> 37:59.451
You're not under arrest.Yet.

37:59.625 --> 38:01.017
This is starting to feel
like delaying

38:01.191 --> 38:02.976
and obstructing
an official investigation.

38:03.150 --> 38:04.673
You know what,
let's just tow his car.

38:04.847 --> 38:06.675
We'll impound it while
we pull the suspect's DNA.

38:07.633 --> 38:09.112
This is
the last driver.

38:10.940 --> 38:13.465
So unless you want us to
charge you with
accessory after the fact,

38:13.639 --> 38:15.075
tell us
where you dropped him off.

38:18.426 --> 38:20.428
♪♪♪♪

38:40.753 --> 38:43.059
You have got
to be kidding me.

38:43.233 --> 38:44.887
[SIGHS]

39:14.917 --> 39:16.092
[GUNSHOT]

39:50.779 --> 39:52.172
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

39:54.261 --> 39:55.305
[SIGHS]

40:01.311 --> 40:02.748
[GROWLS]

40:12.932 --> 40:14.194
[CLATTERING]

40:33.692 --> 40:34.910
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

40:42.875 --> 40:44.703
Come on!
Come on!

40:44.877 --> 40:46.008
Get up!

40:46.182 --> 40:47.401
Who are you?
What do you want?

40:47.575 --> 40:49.882
Don't kill me.
You can have anything.

40:50.622 --> 40:52.232
How about your life back,
huh?

41:00.327 --> 41:02.024
Damn.
We gonna split up, or what?

41:02.198 --> 41:04.200
WALKER: Inside a factory
that's clearly haunted?
Yeah, sure.

41:04.374 --> 41:06.289
What's the worse
that could happen?Why would you say that?

41:06.464 --> 41:08.814
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

41:15.777 --> 41:17.779
Yo, 100 bucks says
there's a pile of dead
clowns in there.

41:17.953 --> 41:19.085
Come on, man.
Why would you
go there with me?

41:19.259 --> 41:20.956
You know my thing
about clowns.

41:21.130 --> 41:21.566
♪♪ Do do do-do-do,
do-do-do do-do ♪♪

41:21.740 --> 41:22.697
Stop it!

41:22.871 --> 41:24.612
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

41:27.310 --> 41:28.747
Save me.

41:28.921 --> 41:30.226
SYD: The human piano keys driving you nuts?

41:30.400 --> 41:31.924
You have no idea.

41:32.098 --> 41:33.578
I hate being
on the sidelines.

41:33.752 --> 41:35.188
I should be
out there with you.

41:35.362 --> 41:37.059
Well, as soon as we bust
Arlo, you can.

41:37.233 --> 41:39.671
So I can go home and shower
the smell of moron off me.

41:40.802 --> 41:42.978
You saw what happened to Ray
when he crossed Mr. Knox.

41:43.152 --> 41:45.111
Let me live,

41:45.285 --> 41:47.461
and you can have
everything you had

41:47.635 --> 41:50.290
before your dickhead brother
got you mixed up
in all of this.

41:52.814 --> 41:54.686
Let me tell you
about my brother, dickhead.

41:59.604 --> 42:03.216
You know, Ray just
always accepted
who we were.

42:05.087 --> 42:06.306
I just never listened.

42:08.221 --> 42:09.439
Well,
I'm listening now.

42:12.965 --> 42:14.923
It's time I started
acting like Ray.

42:15.097 --> 42:18.753
I just want to say,
I really appreciate
everything.

42:19.624 --> 42:20.712
Yeah, I got you.

42:21.800 --> 42:23.628
[GUNSHOTS]

42:23.802 --> 42:25.281
I got to go.

42:25.455 --> 42:26.979
♪♪♪♪

42:32.811 --> 42:34.508
WALKER: LAPD!BAINES: Drop the gun!

42:37.119 --> 42:38.468
[GUN CLATTERS]

42:43.386 --> 42:44.562
Dante.

42:54.659 --> 42:56.617
McKenna,
what's going on?

42:56.791 --> 42:57.836
Do you know this guy?

43:00.273 --> 43:02.884
♪♪♪♪

43:09.456 --> 43:10.588
[HANDCUFFS CLICKING]

43:18.987 --> 43:20.989
You have the right
to remain silent.

43:21.163 --> 43:23.992
Anything you say
can be used against you
in the court of law.

43:25.341 --> 43:27.474
You have the right
to an attorney.

43:27.648 --> 43:29.955
If you cannot afford one, one will be provided for you.

43:31.696 --> 43:34.089
Do you understand the rights
I have just read to you?

43:34.263 --> 43:36.222
DANTE: Yeah.

43:36.396 --> 43:38.398
NANCY: With these rights
in mind, do you wish
to speak to me?

43:38.572 --> 43:39.747
DANTE: You?

43:39.921 --> 43:42.141
No.

43:42.315 --> 43:47.929
♪♪ Like the dust, you settle me

43:50.410 --> 43:56.198
♪♪ And I put my faith
in the skies

43:58.287 --> 44:03.379
♪♪ And my heart into the sea

44:06.861 --> 44:12.562
♪♪ La-da-da-da-da-da-da-da

44:15.087 --> 44:16.523
Warren told me
about Miami.

44:24.270 --> 44:25.793
[SIGHS]

44:29.275 --> 44:30.363
He's a good man.

44:35.542 --> 44:36.848
I know this is
the second time

44:37.022 --> 44:39.807
you've had to come see
your daughter in an ICU

44:39.981 --> 44:41.940
because of something
Gabriel Knox did.

44:45.421 --> 44:47.075
I took it too far.

44:51.514 --> 44:52.864
I know that.

44:54.953 --> 44:56.258
I'm really,
really sorry.

44:56.694 --> 44:57.956
No.

44:58.130 --> 44:59.218
I'm sorry.

44:59.392 --> 45:01.481
No, no, no, no, no.
Come on, don't.

45:02.700 --> 45:04.440
Don't be.

45:04.614 --> 45:06.312
Don't be.

45:06.486 --> 45:08.401
♪♪♪♪

45:14.450 --> 45:16.061
I got a long way to go.

45:18.106 --> 45:19.455
So what do we do now?

45:21.457 --> 45:23.068
Listen, we, uh,

45:23.242 --> 45:25.244
figure out who did this

45:25.418 --> 45:28.813
and make sure
they never hurt us again.

45:28.987 --> 45:30.684
Yeah, that too, Dad.

45:30.858 --> 45:34.253
But I was talking about
this whole family situation.

45:36.995 --> 45:37.952
Oh.Oh.

45:38.126 --> 45:39.084
Oh!

45:39.954 --> 45:41.782
Okay, well...Yeah.

45:42.870 --> 45:44.698
We're gonna work on it.[LAUGHS] Yeah.

45:47.005 --> 45:51.749
♪♪ Ooh ♪♪

45:55.013 --> 45:56.971
[LOCK BEEPS]

45:57.145 --> 45:59.452
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

45:59.626 --> 46:01.628
I need you to stall
on the paperwork.

46:02.629 --> 46:05.023
What?Just drag your feet.

46:05.197 --> 46:06.546
You can't
process it yet.

46:06.720 --> 46:08.026
Of course we can.
He's under arrest.

46:08.200 --> 46:09.592
No, no.
That's not what I mean.

46:09.767 --> 46:13.031
You guys need to book him.
I can't do that.

46:13.205 --> 46:15.076
But just stall.

46:15.250 --> 46:16.686
What the hell
is going on?

46:16.861 --> 46:19.211
Patrick was all over this
earlier, and he...

46:22.910 --> 46:24.390
He's gonna find out...Okay, look,

46:24.564 --> 46:26.044
I'm not trying to get
into your marriage, right?

46:26.218 --> 46:28.176
But whatever you and Syd
got going on,

46:28.350 --> 46:31.136
you been sneaking around here,
keeping secrets for weeks.

46:31.310 --> 46:33.703
Now, I'm your boy,
but I can only look

46:33.878 --> 46:36.054
the other way for so much
before I have to tap out.

46:36.228 --> 46:37.490
You obviously know
this Dante guy.

46:38.752 --> 46:39.927
'Cause clearly he had
something to do with

46:40.101 --> 46:42.495
what went down
in Santa Monica,

46:42.669 --> 46:43.975
and I'd be willing to bet that
this is what Calloway's
all over our asses about.

46:48.893 --> 46:53.158
Look, I-I will tell you guys
the truth about everything,

46:53.332 --> 46:54.724
but it can't be
right now.

46:57.684 --> 46:59.817
Fine.
We'll run interference.

47:01.470 --> 47:03.429
You better come
in here tomorrow
dropping truth bombs.

47:03.603 --> 47:04.909
Thank you.

47:06.258 --> 47:08.608
[MONITORS BEEPING]

47:08.782 --> 47:10.001
[KNOCK ON DOOR, DOOR OPENS]

47:10.175 --> 47:11.089
Hi.

47:11.263 --> 47:12.307
Hey.

47:15.310 --> 47:17.051
I thought you left.

47:17.225 --> 47:19.097
I asked her to stay.Daddy.

47:19.271 --> 47:20.272
Look,
I know what she said

47:20.446 --> 47:21.926
and I know
why she said it,

47:23.014 --> 47:24.319
but you two
need to talk.

47:26.452 --> 47:27.583
We don't have to
do this.

47:27.757 --> 47:29.368
No, you can come in.

47:31.370 --> 47:32.980
You sure?

47:33.154 --> 47:34.634
What else
am I gonna do tonight?

47:38.594 --> 47:40.248
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

47:42.033 --> 47:43.469
What you want to
talk about?

47:47.777 --> 47:49.040
Tell me about Joseph.

47:49.649 --> 47:51.042
Was he a good father?

47:51.956 --> 47:54.262
Actually,
not really.

47:54.436 --> 47:56.351
We had
a terrible relationship.

47:56.525 --> 47:58.701
We didn't work things out
until I was in my 20s.

47:58.876 --> 48:00.225
Really?

48:00.399 --> 48:02.140
Yeah, you probably
built this picture

48:02.314 --> 48:05.273
in your head of
the perfect life with Daddy.

48:05.447 --> 48:07.493
Yep.[CHUCKLES] I get it.

48:08.624 --> 48:10.975
I thought the same thing
about you and your mom.

48:11.149 --> 48:14.108
But just think about, I mean,
he was a single dad.

48:14.282 --> 48:15.805
He really wasn't around
in the beginning,

48:15.980 --> 48:17.416
and then when he was,

48:17.590 --> 48:19.157
well, you know him.

48:20.810 --> 48:22.377
How was he
when you were a kid?

48:23.639 --> 48:24.902
Rough.

48:25.903 --> 48:27.513
The man was rough.

48:27.687 --> 48:29.341
[LAUGHS]Yeah.

48:30.516 --> 48:31.909
But he cared.

48:32.083 --> 48:33.693
That's Daddy.
Same guy.

48:33.867 --> 48:35.695
Did he used to
smoke cigars?

48:35.869 --> 48:38.002
I used to love the way
the yard smelled

48:38.176 --> 48:40.178
after he'd fire one up
after work.

48:41.309 --> 48:43.659
I still like
the smell of cigars.

48:43.833 --> 48:47.272
That house used
to reek of it.

48:47.446 --> 48:50.449
Cigar smoke makes me sick
to my stomach to this day.

48:51.363 --> 48:53.278
And what else?
Tell me something else.

48:53.843 --> 48:55.149
Uh...

48:55.323 --> 48:57.151
He used to love
Lola Falana.

48:57.325 --> 48:58.370
[LAUGHS]

48:58.544 --> 49:00.546
Word.

49:00.720 --> 49:03.201
And, uh, he used to smoke
these cool...[KATHERINE LAUGHING]

49:03.375 --> 49:09.207
♪♪ And I put my faith
in the skies

49:11.513 --> 49:15.343
♪♪ And my heart into the seas

49:15.517 --> 49:17.084
PATRICK: You ready
to be honest with me?

49:17.998 --> 49:20.783
Dante Sherman,
who is he to you?

49:21.871 --> 49:23.743
♪♪ Ah-ah

49:23.917 --> 49:29.488
♪♪ The dust, it settles now ♪♪

49:31.055 --> 49:33.405
♪♪♪♪
